entry.def: A yearbook is a book that is published once a year and that contains information about the events and achievements of the previous year, usually concerning a particular place or organization.

example.tran: 一所美国大学1955年的年刊

means.word_mean: 1. a book published annually by the graduating class of a high school or college usually containing photographs of faculty and graduating students
2. a reference book that is published regularly once every year
